    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tall, three-storied cabinets consisting of a desk between two cupboards and typically decorated with inlay, built in Spain during the 17th century. The name refers to the spindled top story, which form a ventilated food cupboard for fruit, cheese, and bread.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000006971/Burr, Hispanic Furniture (1964)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gabinetes altos de tres pisos, decorados con incrustaciones y consistentes en una mesa de trabajo entre dos aparadores, construidas en España durante el siglo XVII. El piso superior con barrotes forma un aparador para comida ventilado para fruta, queso y pan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grote kasten met drie verdiepingen die met inlegwerk zijn versierd, waarbij een blad tussen twee wandkasten inzit. Ze zijn tijdens de 17e eeuw in Spanje gebouwd. De bovenste laag heeft spijlen ter ventilatie en vormt zo een kast voor fruit, kaas en brood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>三層高櫃，兩個櫃櫥中間有一桌子，通常鑲嵌裝飾，製造於十七世紀的西班牙。該詞彙可指上層支軸形成的夾層，做為通風食櫥以存放水果、起司和麵包。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
